  "prompt": "What is the best dictionary app for iphone?",
  "response": "There are several excellent dictionary apps for iPhone, each offering unique features. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Merriam-Webster Dictionary**: This app offers a robust dictionary, thesaurus, and word games. It includes audio pronunciations, example sentences, and a word of the day feature.\n\n2. **Oxford Dictionary of English**: Known for its comprehensive entries and advanced features, this app provides in-depth definitions, audio pronunciations, and examples in context.\n\n3. **Dictionary.com**: This app offers an extensive database of definitions and synonyms, along with an integrated thesaurus, word games, and the option for offline access.\n\n4. **Cambridge Dictionary**: This app features clear definitions and examples from a range of dictionaries, including English learners' dictionaries, and offers audio pronunciations.\n\n5. **WordWeb**: This is a comprehensive dictionary and thesaurus that works offline. It's known for its simple interface and features like word links and synonyms.\n\n6. **Vocabulary.com**: While not a traditional dictionary, it\u2019s great for learning new words with built-in quizzes and vocabulary builder features.\n\nWhen choosing a dictionary app, consider what features are most important to you, such as offline access, thesaurus capabilities, or learning tools. Many of these apps are free or offer free versions, so you can try them out before committing to a purchase.",
